            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "this is kind of strange. `cmd()` is not going to be invoked unless the config was activated. Nvim already checks `root_markers` and `root_dir` to decide whether to activate a client for a given buffer.\r\n\r\nwhen would this not be the case ? we should avoid reinventing the vim.lsp framework here.",
            "commit_id": "da8d734775e8d38b359f07b5596ba7d9fea8af37",
            "created_at": "2025-06-17T12:56:31Z",
            "diff_hunk": "@@ -22,27 +22,37 @@\n ---   },\n --- })\n \n+function get_cmd()\n+  local useGlobal = vim.lsp.config.glint.init_options.glint.useGlobal\n+  if useGlobal then\n+    return { 'glint-language-server' }\n+  end\n+\n+  local root_markers = vim.lsp.config.glint.root_markers\n+  if not root_markers or #root_markers == 0 then\n+    vim.notify('No root markers defined for glint', vim.log.levels.ERROR)\n+    return nil\n+  end\n+\n+  local root_dir = vim.fs.dirname(vim.fs.find(root_markers, { upward = true })[1])\n+  if not root_dir then\n+    vim.notify('Could not find root directory for glint', vim.log.levels.ERROR)\n+    return nil\n+  end",
